{"info": {"author": "Mustafa Mohamed", "author_email": "ms7mohamed@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy"], "description": "\n# Falcon Query Parameter Verifier\n\nA simple falcon hook to check if a request contains all required query parameters.\n\n***\n\n## Installation / Requirements\n\nInstallation:\n\n**PyPi**\n\n```\npip install falcon_params_verifier\n```\n\n**.whl**\n\nA ``.whl`` is provided in the releases tab in Github. \n\n## Sample Usage\n\n*Sample code*\n\n```python\nimport falcon\nimport falcon_params_verifier \nfrom falcon_params_verifier import ParamVerifier # This can also be used.\n\nclass SampleResource(object):\n    def __init__(self):\n        self._required_params = [\n            \"userId\",\n        ]\n    # Add the hook\n\t@falcon.before(falcon_params_verifier.ParamVerifier(self._required_params))\n    def on_get(self, req, resp):\n        req.media = {\n            \"message\": \"Whoo hoo, you made a proper request!\"\n        }\n```\n\n***\n\nIf a query parameter is missing, the module will automatically raise an ``falcon.HTTPBadRequest``.\n\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/ms7m/falcon-params-verifer", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "falcon-params-verifier", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/falcon-params-verifier/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/falcon-params-verifier/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/ms7m/falcon-params-verifer"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/falcon-params-verifier/0.1.0/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=3.6.0", "summary": "A simple Falcon API \"hook\" to verify if a provided list of query parameters have been fulfilled.", "version": "0.1.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Falcon Query Parameter Verifier</h1>\n<p>A simple falcon hook to check if a request contains all required query parameters.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Installation / Requirements</h2>\n<p>Installation:</p>\n<p><strong>PyPi</strong></p>\n<pre><code>pip install falcon_params_verifier\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>.whl</strong></p>\n<p>A <code>.whl</code> is provided in the releases tab in Github.</p>\n<h2>Sample Usage</h2>\n<p><em>Sample code</em></p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">falcon</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">falcon_params_verifier</span> \n<span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">falcon_params_verifier</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">ParamVerifier</span> <span class=\"c1\"># This can also be used.</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">class</span> <span class=\"nc\">SampleResource</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">object</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"fm\">__init__</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n        <span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">_required_params</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span>\n            <span class=\"s2\">\"userId\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"c1\"># Add the hook</span>\n\t<span class=\"nd\">@falcon</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">before</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">falcon_params_verifier</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ParamVerifier</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">_required_params</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">on_get</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">resp</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">media</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n            <span class=\"s2\">\"message\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"Whoo hoo, you made a proper request!\"</span>\n        <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre>\n<hr>\n<p>If a query parameter is missing, the module will automatically raise an <code>falcon.HTTPBadRequest</code>.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7056628, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "6bf4e462e8e7a1445656d452fc152e90", "sha256": "49278a57a0e63e098c9b32a0cfa0c32bd1bdf5c51561deb587ae1db79b70053e"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "falcon_params_verifier-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "6bf4e462e8e7a1445656d452fc152e90", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6.0", "size": 2815, "upload_time": "2020-04-20T00:33:16", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-20T00:33:16.422653Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/88/0f/aaea0ca0ac4d350a09e598a0fcf5a6644ca6b994d89691847007dbf2840c/falcon_params_verifier-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "cf685132d6e1b074ad4f4ab3d06cceb3", "sha256": "2846ad38bc07dc88def989ba67b31279b7470acc0b4ae513abf28f2413f4f1b2"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "falcon_params_verifier-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "cf685132d6e1b074ad4f4ab3d06cceb3", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.6.0", "size": 2318, "upload_time": "2020-04-20T00:33:18", "upload_time_iso_860